Hevy Workout Analysis — Agentic AI Training Coach

An AI-powered training coach that connects to your [Hevy](https://hevyapp.com) workout data and provides evidence-based programming recommendations using a multi-model agent architecture.
Ask questions about your training in natural language. The agent pulls your real workout history, analyzes volume and gaps, retrieves sports science literature, accounts for your nutrition/training phase, and returns specific programming recommendations with citations.

Example queries:
"My incline bench stalled at 200 lbs and I'm cutting at 2500 cal. What should I adjust?"
"Are my arms getting enough volume?"
"What does the research say about training volume during a deficit?"
"What did I do in my last workout?"

Architecture

User query
    ↓
MoM Router (classifies → selects model)
    ↓
┌──────────┬──────────┬──────────┬──────────┐
│ gpt-4o-  │  gpt-4o  │  direct  │ gpt-4o-  │
│   mini   │          │  lookup  │   mini   │
│(program) │(coaching)│ (no LLM) │(research)│
└──────────┴──────────┴──────────┴──────────┘
    ↓
Tools: Hevy API → Volume Calculator → RAG → Nutrition Checker
    ↓
Anomaly Detection (z-score + Isolation Forest)
    ↓
Structured Output (Pydantic)
    ↓
Eval Harness (LLM-as-judge, 7/7 passing)

Anomaly Detection

Three-layer gap detection system:

1. Rule-based thresholds — flags muscles below minimum effective volume (MEV) from sports science literature (Schoenfeld, Israetel)
2. Z-score per muscle group — compares current week against the user's personal rolling baseline, flags deviations > 1.5σ
3. Isolation Forest — trains on the full weekly volume profile across all muscle groups to detect abnormal overall training patterns

 Eval Suite

7 test scenarios graded by an LLM-as-judge with specific pass/fail criteria:

- 7/7 passing, average score 0.89
- Scenarios include: gap detection, stalled lifts during a cut, deload recommendations, injury modifications, research queries, and data lookups
- Each scenario validates routing accuracy, recommendation quality, safety, and citation of evidence

 Tech Stack

- LangGraph — agent orchestration with conditional routing
- OpenAI — gpt-4o / gpt-4o-mini for generation, text-embedding-3-small for RAG
- ChromaDB — local vector database for sports science literature
- Pydantic — structured outputs for recommendations and analysis
- scikit-learn — Isolation Forest for pattern anomaly detection
- Hevy API — real workout data integration
- Streamlit — dashboard + chat interface
- pytest — eval harness with LLM-as-judge scoring

 Setup

 Prerequisites

- Python 3.12
- [Hevy Pro](https://hevyapp.com) account (for API access)
- OpenAI API key

 Install

bash
git clone https://github.com/pnair0703/hevy_workout_analysis.git
cd hevy_workout_analysis
python3.12 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install httpx pydantic python-dotenv chromadb openai langgraph langchain-core langchain-openai scikit-learn numpy streamlit pytest


 Configure

bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your keys:
#   HEVY_API_KEY=your_hevy_api_key
#   OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key


Get your Hevy API key at [hevy.com/settings?developer](https://hevy.com/settings?developer).

 Run

bash
# Dashboard + chat UI
streamlit run frontend/app.py

# Run the agent directly
python test_agent.py

# Run eval suite
pytest evals/run_evals.py -v -s

# Test individual components
python test_hevy.py       # Hevy API connection
python test_rag.py        # RAG pipeline + nutrition
python test_anomaly.py    # Anomaly detection


 Project Structure


hevy_workout_analysis/
├── frontend/
│   └── app.py                 # Streamlit UI (dashboard + chat)
├── src/
│   ├── agent/
│   │   ├── graph.py           # LangGraph pipeline
│   │   ├── nodes.py           # Agent nodes (router, tools, synthesizer)
│   │   ├── router.py          # MoM query classifier
│   │   └── state.py           # Agent state definition
│   ├── tools/
│   │   ├── hevy.py            # Hevy API client
│   │   ├── volume_calc.py     # Volume analysis + gap detection
│   │   ├── anomaly.py         # Z-score + Isolation Forest
│   │   ├── rag.py             # RAG pipeline (Chroma + OpenAI embeddings)
│   │   └── nutrition.py       # Phase-aware nutrition constraints
│   ├── models/
│   │   ├── workout.py         # Pydantic models for Hevy data
│   │   └── program.py         # Pydantic models for recommendations
│   └── data/
│       └── knowledge/         # Sports science docs for RAG
└── evals/
    ├── run_evals.py           # LLM-as-judge eval runner
    ├── scenarios/
    │   └── test_scenarios.json # 7 test cases
    └── judges/
        └── judge_prompts.py   # Judge prompt templates


 Eval Results

| Scenario | Score | Route |
|---|---|---|
| Critical chest volume gap | 0.75 | coaching → gpt-4o |
| Stalled bench during cut | 0.75 | coaching → gpt-4o |
| Overreaching / deload | 1.00 | coaching → gpt-4o |
| Shoulder injury modification | 1.00 | coaching → gpt-4o |
| Research: volume during deficit | 1.00 | research → gpt-4o-mini |
| Arm volume gap identification | 0.75 | coaching → gpt-4o |
| Simple data lookup | 1.00 | lookup → none |

